item.description:
invalid: <p>
The issue isn't with <code>is_singular()</code> or <code>is_single()</code> - the issue is that your conditional logic affects all queries on the page instead of just the main query.
</p>
<p>
The template conditional functions refer to the main query (ie. the main loop), but you're not accounting for the fact that not every query is the main query.
</p>
<p>
Your conditional logic should use <code>is_main_query()</code> and should look something like this:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function my_add_custom_content( $title) {
	if ( is_main_query() &amp;&amp; is_singular( 'events' ) ):
		$postID = get_the_ID();
		$html = '&lt;a href="#" class="goingLink setGoing" id="'.$postID.'" data-value="'. $postID .'"&gt;I\'m Going&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div id="fb-root"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';
		$title .= $html;
	endif;
	return $title;
}
</pre>
